This application uses React for the frontend and python3 for backend.

In order to run, make sure to have the following installed:

-npm
-docker
-docker-compose
-python3-pip

For app initialization, run the following:

sudo docker compose up team-db user-db task-db

After that, run ./restore.sh
In case the above does not work, simply copy the commands located inside and execute them seperately.

Then, sudo docker compose down.

The above section will ensure that the databases have been properly initialized with the tables and some example data.

The main command is the following:

sudo IP=$(curl ifconfig.me) docker compose up --build

This will fetch our public IP which the frontend will listen to
and it will build the 3 microservices with the required python modules.


To connect to the site, simply type the IP of the host machine that the app is running into
a browser and nginx engine will automatically expose the required port.